content: Understood, that is a clear and concise format for the data you have provided. The columns and data types are well defined, which makes it easy to understand the structure of the data and perform analysis. The use of a timestamp data type for the "changeDateTime" and "createdAt" columns will allow you to perform time-based analysis on the data, such as tracking the distribution of business registrations over time. The "classificationDescription" column provides information on the business sector, while the "postCodes" column allows you to analyze the distribution of business registrations across different regions.
